The paper presents an algorithm for building probabilistic rule lists, which is a type of associative classifier. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically in the area of classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
